refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.parameters;


  hostname


    The hostname or IPv6 address whose location is to be looked-up.

&reftitle.returnvalues;

 Returns the two letter ISO country code on success, or &false;
 if the address cannot be found in the database.

  &reftitle.examples;

   A geoip_country_code_by_name_v6 example

    This will print where the IPv6 address is located.



<?php
$country = geoip_country_code_by_name_v6('2a00:1450:4007:80f::200e');
if ($country) {
    echo 'This host is located in: ' . $country;
}
?>


   &example.outputs;


This host is located in: US
